Next, prediction models combining both prior ZIKV case counts and Twitter data to estimate weekly ZIKV case counts were explored. Specifically, we applied an auto-regressive (AR) model using zika tweet counts as an input series. Two types of covariates were used; namely, prior weekly ZIKV case counts and prior weekly zika tweet counts. Prior to model development, first-order differencing was applied to both dependent and independent variables. This is standard practice to address the issue of stationarity that is common to time-series data. After differencing, we examined various models using 1–6 week lags [AR(1,1)-AR [1, 6]] for both the auto-regressive variable as well as the tweet variable according to the following general equation:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
